gomodel:SYNGO_1786  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Strong activation of synaptic NMDARs induced hippocalcin-YFP translocation to dendritic spines.\"\nFig.5: \"Activation of synaptic and total pools of NMDARs resulted in differential hippocalcin-YFP signalling in spines.\"\nFig.6: \"Intrinsic bursts of network activity induced hippocalcin-YFP translocation to dendritic spines\". Experimental description: Experiments were done rats\nLiteral \"Neurons were obtained from newborn Wistar rats ...\"\n\n17/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed protein is of rat species (traced back to PIMID:11836243): \"The EYFP-tagged hippocalcin fusion construct (pHippo-EYFP) was made by the in-frame insertion of a hippocalcin sequence, amplified from rat brain cDNA, ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1786" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

